Name: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
Definition: A hypogonadism characterized by a impaired signalling by gonadotrpin relasing hormone.

Name: gonadal dysgenesis
Definition: A hypogonadism that is characterized by a progressive loss of germ cells on the developing gonads of an embryo.

Name: eunuchism
Definition: A hypogonadism that is characterized by the lack of mature male germ cells and testicular hormones.

Name: obsolete adult primary liver cancer
Definition: A hypogonadism that is characterized by the lack of mature male germ cells and testicular hormones.
Synonym: adult primary cancer of the Liver

Name: obsolete resectable hepatocellular carcinoma
Definition: A hypogonadism that is characterized by the lack of mature male germ cells and testicular hormones.
